<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I, too, am a little disgruntled at the failure rate. However, the success rate seems to be improving as my skill goes up. There was a definite detriment to it the one time I forgot to exchange the charisma items I was wearing to the wisdom ones. I have also seen discussions that dexterity might improve the success rate.<br>
I am not expert at the places some things are obtained, but in my limited travels I have found that the crag spiders in EK seem to drop the most silks on a consistent basis...although one time I did have four in a row with no silk...other times they can drop 6 and once I think we saw 7 silks on one spider! Definitely the best rate of drop that I have found, tho they take much more mana than other spiders. I was kiting and soloing them (I'm a druid) and still getting exp from some at level 30. I started soloing them late, though, and they were blue to me at 26, if I remember correctly. I obtained 3 levels just soloing the crags.<br>
And after level 30...well, you don't get exp, <br>
but until I find spiders that will consistently drop at least two silks with little mana expense, I will use crags to get silks, I think.<br>
A note for Brewers: I go back to Misty often to get spiderling silks, and I find that they drop spider legs (in addition to spiderling legs) fairly often.<br>
Another note: It is wonderful to see the expansion of the trade skills with new recipes. The "cultural" armor is confusing to say the least, and the use of the "imbued plains pebble" is still not clear to me. I bought the spell from Tak Whistler in NK, but yesterday, someone informed me that he was not selling spells anymore...or perhaps they meant that he was not located at the druid ring???? I didn't have the time to check this for accuracy. I used the spell on some pebbles, and the nice thing is that they now are stackable. I am assuming that it will be used in making the cultural armor. I surely hope it will be useable by halflings. I am assuming that since I have seen some recipes for cultural armor, but none are up yet for halflings, at least at EQTradersCorner. I followed a link from that site to here, and if there is information here about it that I have not investigated yet, then I apologize.<hr>Yewset Silvermist<br>
Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
