<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">hmmm... my char has a geared up wis of about 135 I think now (miserable int tho.. 63).  It took forever to get skills up, but now I rarely fail (btw there is -always- a 5% chance of failure, no matter how good you are, just as there is always a 5% chance of success, no matter how bad you are).  Wis is the success rate indicator, so if you want to succeed, that's where to put your points or money for magic items.  Btw, my char's charisma sux (barb shaman), so I don't ever break even.<p>

You -could- make an enchanter with about 100/100 int/wis and that would give you quick successes, but not nearly as consistent successes as a low int, hi wis character.<p>

Merro<br>
